Fourth Department, June, 1966

(June 17, 1966) Patricia D. Lockhart, an Infant, by Jeanne Lockhart, Her Guardian ad Litem, et al., Respondents, v. County of Erie et al., Appellants.

Appeal unanimously dismissed, without costs. Memorandum: The order before us is *610not appealable. (See Govell v. H. B. H. Constr. Corp., 17 N Y 2d 709.) (Appeal from order of Erie Trial Term which denied defendant’s motion for a directed verdict on the complaint or for a dismissal of the complaint.) Present — Williams, P. J., Goldman, Henry, Del Vecchio and Marsh, JJ.
